# warden CLI configuration (env-file form) — OPTIONAL.
#
# The CLI targets https://nyxtra.dev out of the box; you do not need this file.
# It exists only to point the CLI at a NON-production deployment (local dev,
# a preview). The CLI reads WARDEN_* keys from ./.env (copy this file) and from
# ~/.warden/env. Real environment variables and --flags always win.

# Uncomment to make `warden login` target a local Nyxtra dev server
# (http://localhost:5173, `npm run dev` in the nyxtra-website repo) instead of
# production. Leave commented for normal (production) use.
#WARDEN_ENV=dev

# Or pin an exact deployment (beats WARDEN_ENV):
#WARDEN_ISSUER=https://nyxtra.dev
